elements.title: Let Us Continue
elements.contents: ... that Lyndon B. Johnson (pictured) delivered the "Let Us Continue" address five days after assuming the presidency upon the assassination of John F. Kennedy?

elements.title: pushbacks of migrants
elements.contents: ... that pushbacks of migrants in the Aegean Sea have been described as "a human rights violation that encapsulates a will to eliminate a person's presence on the face of the planet"?

elements.title: Larry Smyth
elements.contents: ... that when Oregon journalist Larry Smyth was asked who he thought would win presidential elections, he invariably replied "the man who gets the most votes"?

elements.title: Central Khalsa Orphanage

elements.title: KOPR-TV
elements.contents: ... that Montana television station KOPR-TV brought forward its start date by several months, only to last just one year?

elements.title: Esther Ze Naw
elements.contents: ... that Esther Ze Naw, who appeared on the 2021 Time 100, was one of the few people in Myanmar who protested against Aung San Suu Kyi's defence of the military at the International Court of Justice in December 2019?
